  "content": "ID: T1137.003\nTitle: Office Application Startup:Outlook Forms\nURL: https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1137/003\nAdversaries may abuse Microsoft Outlook forms to obtain persistence on a compromised system. Outlook forms are used as templates for presentation and functionality in Outlook messages. Custom Outlook forms can be created that will execute code when a specifically crafted email is sent by an adversary utilizing the same custom Outlook form. [1] Once malicious forms have been added to the user’s mailbox, they will be loaded when Outlook is started. Malicious forms will execute when an adversary sends a specifically crafted email to the user. [1]",
  "category": "Article",
